article.headline: Evansville 80, Lipscomb 73
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Matt Webster scored a career-high 33 points and hit 20 free throws as Evansville held off Lipscomb 80-73 on Saturday night. Evansville went to the line 43 times as Lipscomb was called for 33 fouls. Kyle Anslinger added 15 points for the Aces (7-3) who won for the seventh time in eight games. Brian Fisk led Lipscomb (7-4) with 18 points as the Bisons hit six first-half 3-pointers and trailed 36-32 at halftime. After Trey Williams hit a 3-pointer to give Lipscomb a 62-60 lead late in the game, Webster scored 12 points in the final 4:24 to fuel a 20-11 Evansville run and seal the victory. Art Stalbergs came off the bench to score 11 points for the Aces, whose reserves outscored the Lipscomb bench 20-10.
